column2: sampleCount        Total number of samples taken by this sampler.
column3: sampleTime        Total amount of time spent taking samples.
column4: delayDuration        Actual duration of sampling delay taken before taking this sample.
column5: statResources        Current number of statistic resources being sampled by this sampler.
column6: jvmPauses        Total number of JVM pauses (which may or may not be full GC pauses) detected by this sampler. A JVM pause is defined as a system event which kept the statistics sampler thread from sampling for 3000 or more milliseconds. This threshold can be customized by setting the system property gemfire.statSamplerDelayThreshold (units are milliseconds).
